Yale Repertory Theatre

2019-20 Season

   From Will Eno’s The Plot to Lorraine Hansberry’s A Raisin in the Sun,
   another extraordinary season is under way at the Yale Rep.

   [Image from the recent production of Girls. Credit: Joan Marcus.]
   Learn more The Feature Archive
   The Feature Archive
   Performing Arts at Yale
   (BUTTON) Previous (BUTTON) Next
   (BUTTON) Previous (BUTTON) Next

Yale School of Drama

Student productions

   The school stages several productions during the academic year. Explore
   this season’s offerings, including Fun Home and the Langston Hughes
   Festival of New Work.

Alliance for Dance at Yale

Undergraduate Groups

   This umbrella organization unites the 24 groups in Yale College and
   connects Yale with the New Haven dance community​.

The Yale Cabaret

Experimental theater

   Now in its 52nd season, the Cabaret aims “to revitalize and rekindle
   the hearts and minds of those who seek to explore their full artistic
   potential.”

